text.tspan: Cancer death rates in children under 5 years old
Reported annual death rate from childhood cancers, per 100,000 children aged under five, based on the

underlying cause
listed on death certificates. This is shown for all malignant cancers combined, brain and nervous
system cancers, leukemia , lymphomas and multiple myeloma .
